# Vision Statement

My journey so far, from growing in senior high to leading in our capstone and engaging with the LV Science Club, has taught me the value of communication, initiative, and connection. These experiences shaped how I see my role in CPI.

If given the chance to serve, my priorities are:

-First Choice → Contribute to a committee where I can apply my strengths in teamwork and initiative.  
-Second Choice → Support an area that allows me to build connections and represent CPI through active involvement.  
-Third Choice: COMPRI → I am also open to serving in COMPRI, where I can use my communication skills to help share information, strengthen CPI’s image, and ensure students feel informed and included.  

My vision is to help CPI not just share information, but build trust and connection with students. I believe communication is more than announcements; it is about making people feel included and engaged. That is the mindset I want to bring into whichever committee I serve.
